<subSubSection id="C34F8499FFAE9365FF75FC58FC03FA40" pageId="6" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAE9365FF75FC58FB04FAEF" blockId="6.[151,1437,963,1422]" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FF75FC58FD65FC10" bold="true" box="[151,678,963,989]" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Description derived from earlier literature.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FD52FC5FFD38FC10" box="[688,763,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Facies</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136ECB97FFAE9365FCEFFC58FCA5FC10" box="[781,870,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–50" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[232,1322,222,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[151,1436,178,1758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40–50. Aethina (Aethina) argus Grouvelle, 1890: 40, Dorsal facies, line drawing (adapted from Grouvelle, 1890); 41, Tegmen, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 42, Median lobe, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 43. A. (A.) cyaneipennis Grouvelle, 1903: Dorsal facies (line drawing adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 44–50. A. (A.) inconspicua Nakane, 1967 (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986): 44, Tegmen of specimen from Punjab; 45, 47, Median lobe and 48, Tegmen of specimen from S. China; 46, Median lobe of specimen from Punjab; 49, Dorsal facies of specimen from Fuji; 50, Dorsal facies of specimen from Punjab." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417015/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
): Body colour entirely testaceous-ferrugineous, a little darkened with ten black punctate spots; four on the pronotum: the first in the middle of anterior margin, the second above the scutellar shield near posterior margin, and two postero-laterally placed; five on the elytra: one sutural, and two on each sides of elytron; one in the middle of last abdominal segment. Body rather broad, oval, subconvex, densely punctate. Cuticle covered with decumbent pubescence, more distinct than base of elytra. Antennae testaceous. 
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FE6BFBECFE38FB5C" box="[393,507,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Prothorax</emphasis>
transverse, slightly narrowed anterad, anterior margin deeply emarginate, posterior corners of pronotum somewhat projecting posterad. 
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FD3EFB00FC48FB78" box="[732,907,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Scutellar shield</emphasis>
transverse, punctate. 
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FB9EFB00FB01FB78" box="[1148,1218,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Elytra</emphasis>
with truncate apex, exposing only the last abdominal segment. 
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FD9EFB24FD25FB14" box="[636,742,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Abdomen</emphasis>
and metaventrite finely punctate, a little near sides. 
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FACDFB24FA5FFB14" box="[1327,1436,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136ECB97FFAE9365FF7DFB78FEEEFB30" box="[159,301,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–50" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[232,1322,222,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[151,1436,178,1758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40–50. Aethina (Aethina) argus Grouvelle, 1890: 40, Dorsal facies, line drawing (adapted from Grouvelle, 1890); 41, Tegmen, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 42, Median lobe, line drawing (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 43. A. (A.) cyaneipennis Grouvelle, 1903: Dorsal facies (line drawing adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 44–50. A. (A.) inconspicua Nakane, 1967 (adapted from Kirejtshuk, 1986): 44, Tegmen of specimen from Punjab; 45, 47, Median lobe and 48, Tegmen of specimen from S. China; 46, Median lobe of specimen from Punjab; 49, Dorsal facies of specimen from Fuji; 50, Dorsal facies of specimen from Punjab." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417015/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Figs. 41, 42</figureCitation>
): Tegmen elongate, tongue-shaped, subparallel sides with rounded apex; row of setae present in the apical third at the sides. Median lobe bud shaped, slightly longer than broad with rounded apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAE9365FF25FAB7FC6FFA88" blockId="6.[151,1437,963,1422]" box="[199,940,1323,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FF25FAB7FEAAFA88" box="[199,361,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Measurements</emphasis>
(in mm.): Total length 3.8–6.6; total width 2.4–3.8.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAE9365FF25FAD4FB1AFAA4" blockId="6.[151,1437,963,1422]" box="[199,1241,1359,1386]" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAE9365FF25FAD4FE58FAA4" box="[199,411,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="539">Material examined</emphasis>
: The material could not be examined due to non-availability of specimen.
</paragraph>
